==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sturt
<hw>Sturt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Start</er>,
<pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>To vex; to annoy; to startle.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sturt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sturt
<hw>Sturt</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Disturbance; annoyance;
care.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sturt</xex> and care.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J.
Rolland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>A bargain in tribute mining by
which the tributor profits.</def> <rj><au>Raymond.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sturtion</ent>⟦br⟧
